{"bugs": [
  {
    "description": "Infinite loop in `getImpureBooleanValue` method for `Token.HOOK` case when `trueValue` and `falseValue` are not equal. It should return `TernaryValue.UNKNOWN` regardless of the comparison result."
  },
  {
    "description": "Null pointer exception can occur in `getStringValue` method when the node type is `Token.NAME` and the string value is not one of the predefined keywords (undefined, Infinity, NaN). The method should check if the string value is null before accessing it."
  },
  {
    "description": "In `getPureBooleanValue` method, the `Token.NUMBER` case is not handling negative zero (0.0) correctly. It should return `TernaryValue.FALSE` for negative zero to match the behavior of the `Boolean()` cast function."
  }
]}
